Annotation: Analyst Upgrades: Multiple analysts upgraded Elastic stock citing strong Q3 results.
Stock Surge: Shares jumped nearly 13% following earnings and upgrades.
Fiscal Q3 2025 Earnings: Revenue $382.1M; EPS $0.63, boosted by AI products.
New CFO Appointment: Navam Welihinda appointed CFO with extensive finance experience.
New CRO Appointment: Mark Dodds appointed CRO to drive revenue growth.
Product Update: Launched Logsdb Index Mode, reducing log storage footprint by 65%.
AI Ecosystem Launch: Launched AI ecosystem to support generative AI app development.
Analyst Upgrade: Wedbush upgraded Elastic, citing strong AI potential.
Fiscal Q2 2025 Earnings: Revenue $382.1M; EPS $0.63 driven by AI demand.
Fiscal Q1 2025 Earnings: Reported sales execution issues; regional spending declined.
Open Source Announcement: Elasticsearch and Kibana returned to an open-source license under GNU AGPL, enabling greater community collaboration and transparency.
Fiscal Q4 2024 Earnings: Strong Q4 earnings: $335M revenue, $0.21 EPS.
Cohere Integration: Integrated Cohere's text embedding models to enhance Elasticsearch.
Elastic Excellence Awards: Awarded organizations for innovative Elastic implementations.
Fiscal Q3 2024 Earnings: Revenue of $347.4M and EPS of $0.36 exceeded estimates.
Product Launch: Launched Elasticsearch Relevance Engine and new security features.
Elastic Security Enhancement: Launched advanced XDR enhancements in Elastic Security.
Q2 FY23 Earnings: Exceeded revenue estimates, highlighting strength in cloud services.
Headcount Reduction: Reduced workforce by 13% due to macroeconomic pressures.
Partnership with Microsoft Azure: Partnership announced with Azure to enhance observability.
Acquisition of Optimyze: Acquired cloud computing firm Optimyze.
Acquisition of Cmd: Acquired Cmd, enhancing Linux monitoring capabilities.
Acquisition of build.security: Acquired build.security to enhance cloud security.
New CEO Appointment: Ashutosh Kulkarni appointed as CEO, succeeding Shay Banon.
Q2 FY21 Earnings: Exceeded earnings expectations; raised future guidance.
Acquisition of Endgame: Acquired Endgame, expanding security capabilities.
Q4 2019 Earnings: Reported strong Q4 earnings, 63% YoY revenue growth.
IPO: Elastic went public on NYSE under the symbol ESTC at $70 per share.
